Sure am sorry about your brother,
Freddie.

357
00:29:40.112 --> 00:29:41.904
Old Willard too.

358
00:29:42.072 --> 00:29:44.407
Good boys, both.

359
00:29:49.163 --> 00:29:52.206
Ten years ago, that nigger would
be hanging by the end of a rope...

360
00:29:52.374 --> 00:29:54.292
with his balls in his mouth.

361
00:29:54.460 --> 00:29:56.627
You tell me what's wrong
with this country.

362
00:29:57.379 --> 00:29:58.921
Klan would know what to do.

363
00:30:00.048 --> 00:30:02.008
My granddaddy, he was Klan.

364
00:30:03.093 --> 00:30:07.054
- Ain't no Klan around here for years.
- Oh, there's still some boys around.

365
00:30:07.222 --> 00:30:09.515
Them skinheads who want to
blow up the government?

366
00:30:09.683 --> 00:30:12.810
No, sir. Good God-fearing Klan.

367
00:30:15.189 --> 00:30:17.607
I got a friend, used to be active.

368
00:30:17.774 --> 00:30:18.900
I could give him a call.

369
00:30:20.736 --> 00:30:22.778
You do that, Winston.

370
00:30:22.946 --> 00:30:25.823
You tell them boys we need
some Klan down here in Canton.

371
00:30:25.991 --> 00:30:28.034
I mean right quick.

372
00:30:31.413 --> 00:30:32.455
Hurry up, honey.

373
00:30:32.623 --> 00:30:34.123
Coming, coming, coming.

374
00:30:34.291 --> 00:30:37.418
- Something you can tell us?
- What did Carl Lee tell you?

375
00:30:37.586 --> 00:30:39.212
There's Ozzie.

376
00:30:40.589 --> 00:30:44.759
- To our family's television debut.
- To the big time.

377
00:30:45.385 --> 00:30:49.138
I cannot believe he didn't take you seriously
when you warned him.

378
00:30:49.306 --> 00:30:52.683
Well, baby, you know, some folks
think those boys got what they deserved.

379
00:30:52.851 --> 00:30:56.187
Here, sweet pea. Carl Lee Hailey
may very well spend his life in prison.

380
00:30:56.355 --> 00:30:58.147
That is nothing his family deserves.

381
00:30:58.315 --> 00:30:59.607
- Yeah.
- You did call Ozzie—

382
00:30:59.775 --> 00:31:02.443
- Lookit here. Look who's—
