493
00:37:16.860 --> 00:37:19.194
And I lost my job at the mill.

494
00:37:19.362 --> 00:37:20.529
They called Gwen.

495
00:37:20.697 --> 00:37:24.783
Worked 20 years,
I'm out five days and they fired me.

496
00:37:27.162 --> 00:37:31.624
Carl Lee, I can't try
a capital-murder case for $900.

497
00:37:31.791 --> 00:37:33.584
Carl Lee, I need to live.

498
00:37:33.752 --> 00:37:35.502
Me too, Jake.

499
00:37:35.670 --> 00:37:37.254
I need to live too.

500
00:37:46.973 --> 00:37:48.807
Nice night.

501
00:37:54.356 --> 00:37:57.524
Finder of precedents,
mystery woman of the courthouse.

502
00:37:57.692 --> 00:38:00.653
Yup. Care for a beer?

503
00:38:03.406 --> 00:38:06.492
I assume that's the infamous
change-of-venue motion under your arm.

504
00:38:06.660 --> 00:38:08.327
Mm-hm.

505
00:38:08.495 --> 00:38:09.870
Ellen Roark. R-O-A-R-K.

506
00:38:10.038 --> 00:38:13.749
That's Roark in Boston,
but it seems to be Roark in Mississippi.

507
00:38:13.917 --> 00:38:16.210
- Boston, huh?
- Yup, I was born there.

508
00:38:16.378 --> 00:38:18.796
My father's the notorious Sheldon Roark.

509
00:38:18.964 --> 00:38:20.547
Attorney to the stars, yes.

510
00:38:20.715 --> 00:38:22.257
Duly impressed.

511
00:38:22.425 --> 00:38:25.511
What brings you to Mississippi, Roark?
Slumming?

512
00:38:25.679 --> 00:38:27.680
No, law school at Ole Miss.

513
00:38:27.847 --> 00:38:29.932
It's a... It's a family tradition.

514
00:38:30.100 --> 00:38:34.228
Mom was a sweet little sorority girl there
till Dad— Till Dad married her.

515
00:38:34.396 --> 00:38:37.731
I married a sweet little sorority girl
from Ole Miss myself.

516
00:38:37.899 --> 00:38:41.151
- Well, they have an excellent selection.
- Yes, they do.

517
00:38:41.319 --> 00:38:43.153
Now, really, what brings you to Canton?

518
00:38:43.321 --> 00:38:45.906
I'm not believing they don't have cars
to sit on on campus.

519
00:38:46.074 --> 00:38:47.449
Carl Lee Hailey.

520
00:38:49.995 --> 00:38:52.246
Really like to help you with the trial.

521
00:38:52.414 --> 00:38:54.289
Now, what makes you think I need help?

522
00:38:55.041 --> 00:38:57.292
You're trying one of the largest
murder cases...

523
00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:59.920
these parts have seen
and you work alone.

524
00:39:00.088 --> 00:39:02.339
You have no paralegals,
no clerks, researchers...

525
00:39:02.507 --> 00:39:04.466
nor can you afford to hire any...

526
00:39:04.634 --> 00:39:08.262
so if Noose doesn't accept
that motion under your arm...

527
00:39:08.430 --> 00:39:13.017
you go to trial in less than a month.
Trust me, you need help.

528
00:39:13.184 --> 00:39:16.937
- Now, how do you know this?
- Well, I'm an excellent researcher.

529
00:39:17.105 --> 00:39:19.148
- I see that.
- Look, I've played gofer...

530
00:39:19.315 --> 00:39:22.109
for 7 capital-murder cases,
I've witnessed 2 executions...

531
00:39:22.277 --> 00:39:26.488
I have written briefs for the ACLU,
I'm top 5 percent of my class...

532
00:39:26.656 --> 00:39:30.117
editor of the law review,
I'm published, I'm young.

533
00:39:30.285 --> 00:39:31.410
And when I graduate...

534
00:39:31.578 --> 00:39:35.873
I intend to spend a glorious career
stomping out the death penalty.

535
00:39:36.499 --> 00:39:39.752
Let's see, what else?
Oh, genius runs in my family.

536
00:39:39.919 --> 00:39:41.295
You'll get me on the way up...

537
00:39:41.463 --> 00:39:45.215
and I really think, you know,
now is a good time to, you know, grab me.

538
00:39:45.383 --> 00:39:48.093
Mm-hm.
Is there anything else I should know?

539
00:39:48.261 --> 00:39:50.471
Uh, let's see, anything else?

540
00:39:50.638 --> 00:39:53.098
Oh, my father's filthy rich,
so I'll work for free.

541
00:39:55.393 --> 00:39:56.643
What do you think?

542
00:39:59.814 --> 00:40:02.649
I think I'll drop this brief off
in Noose's night slot.

543
00:40:03.234 --> 00:40:04.985
Go home and see my family.

544
00:40:05.153 --> 00:40:08.822
Thank you, Roark,
but I can handle the case myself.

545
00:40:10.992 --> 00:40:12.618
Uh...

546
00:40:12.786 --> 00:40:14.912
You might wanna
look at these precedents.

547
00:40:15.080 --> 00:40:17.623
Look at State v. Cooper
and State v. Roundtree.

548
00:40:17.791 --> 00:40:20.209
Both revenge killers, both acquitted.

549
00:40:23.505 --> 00:40:25.130
You'll change your mind.

550
00:40:27.300 --> 00:40:28.884
See you.

551
00:40:35.266 --> 00:40:37.684
Get out. Come on.

552
00:40:40.021 --> 00:40:41.021
Wait.

553
00:40:41.189 --> 00:40:42.731
Come on.

554
00:41:04.838 --> 00:41:10.008
Mr. Cobb, this is Stump Sisson,
grand dragon of Mississippi.

555
00:41:11.678 --> 00:41:14.012
He heard you were looking to see us.

556
00:41:14.889 --> 00:41:17.599
You were right to call us, Mr. Cobb.

557
00:41:18.726 --> 00:41:21.061
They say the Klan is dead.

558
00:41:22.647 --> 00:41:27.651
Klan don't show up for a few years
and people say the Klan is dead.

559
00:41:28.069 --> 00:41:30.779
Fact is, it just looks dead.

560
00:41:30.947 --> 00:41:34.158
The Klan has always been right there...

561
00:41:34.325 --> 00:41:36.493
under the surface.

562
00:41:37.328 --> 00:41:41.874
Just waiting for the opportunity
to deliver God's justice.

563
00:41:42.917 --> 00:41:44.251
I wanna help.

564
00:41:44.419 --> 00:41:46.420
I wanna kill that nigger.

565
00:41:46.588 --> 00:41:50.299
Niggers got plenty
of protection nowadays.

566
00:41:51.134 --> 00:41:55.596
They got the NAACP and the ACLU.

567
00:41:55.763 --> 00:41:58.098
Even the federal government.

568
00:41:58.266 --> 00:41:59.892
Hell.

569
00:42:00.101 --> 00:42:02.978
White folks ain't got a chance.

570
00:42:04.022 --> 00:42:06.064
Except the Klan.

571
00:42:09.986 --> 00:42:11.570
I'm gonna tell you what.

572
00:42:13.489 --> 00:42:16.992
You get five or six of your friends
of similar thinking...

573
00:42:17.160 --> 00:42:21.455
and we'll initiate
the Madison County Klavern.

574
00:42:22.874 --> 00:42:24.791
Even make you leader.

575
00:42:27.253 --> 00:42:29.046
Now, you tell me...

576
00:42:29.380 --> 00:42:30.964
who's that nigger's lawyer?

577
00:42:32.008 --> 00:42:33.217
Local boy.

578
00:42:33.384 --> 00:42:36.678
His name's Brigance.
He's got a pretty good reputation.

579
00:42:38.765 --> 00:42:40.098
He got family?

580
00:42:40.266 --> 00:42:44.019
Yes, sir. He...
He has a wife and a daughter.

581
00:42:46.981 --> 00:42:48.357
Good.

582
00:43:08.127 --> 00:43:09.878
Two, two.

583
00:43:29.899 --> 00:43:32.234
- What the hell is he doing here?
- Now, calm down.

584
00:43:32.402 --> 00:43:34.069
- No.
- Come on, calm down.

585
00:43:34.237 --> 00:43:38.115
- Calm down.
- He has no right after what he did.

586
00:43:38.283 --> 00:43:40.075
No, he's got no right, sheriff.

587
00:43:40.243 --> 00:43:42.661
Don't get your mom upset now.

588
00:43:56.050 --> 00:43:57.759
Looney?

589
00:43:58.761 --> 00:44:00.012
Dwayne?

590
00:44:04.600 --> 00:44:07.394
I made Ozzie bring me.

591
00:44:12.108 --> 00:44:14.026
Shit, Dwayne, we—

592
00:44:14.193 --> 00:44:16.236
We known each other
since we was kids.

593
00:44:21.534 --> 00:44:22.909
It's my fault.

594
00:44:24.037 --> 00:44:25.746
No matter what gets said in court...

595
00:44:27.206 --> 00:44:31.501
I knew what I was doing,
and I sure didn't intend to hurt you...

596
00:44:31.669 --> 00:44:33.086
but just them two boys.

597
00:44:38.593 --> 00:44:41.636
I know it don't mean much now...

598
00:44:42.680 --> 00:44:43.889
but I'm sorry.

599
00:44:52.023 --> 00:44:55.650
Some folks think that a black man
cannot receive a fair trial in the South.

600
00:44:56.110 --> 00:45:00.113
I intend to show the men and women of
the South will look past color and see truth.

601
00:45:00.281 --> 00:45:01.948
It sure is a nigger's world.

602
00:45:02.116 --> 00:45:03.575
Not for long.

603
00:45:05.787 --> 00:45:10.123
Boys, I am very proud
to invite you to become soldiers...

604
00:45:10.291 --> 00:45:13.293
in the war to protect
our Christian homes and families.

605
00:45:13.461 --> 00:45:18.256
To resurrect our country
from the fires of racial degradation.

606
00:45:18.424 --> 00:45:24.179
And to make white people
the sole masters of our nation's destiny.

607
00:45:24.639 --> 00:45:26.932
What I'm saying, fellas...

608
00:45:27.642 --> 00:45:29.601
it's time for the nigger to pay.

609
00:45:32.647 --> 00:45:36.691
- Something wrong with your telephone?
- No, we just had the number changed.

610
00:45:36.859 --> 00:45:38.568
That's what the operator said.

611
00:45:38.736 --> 00:45:40.862
- To an unlisted number.
- Yeah.

612
00:45:41.030 --> 00:45:43.156
I'm sorry you had to
come all the way up here.

613
00:45:43.324 --> 00:45:45.158
I should've called you, but this case—

614
00:45:45.326 --> 00:45:49.079
This case has us all worried sick
about you all, Jake.

615
00:45:49.247 --> 00:45:52.999
And you know this thing could get ugly.
And dangerous.

616
00:45:53.167 --> 00:45:56.461
Jake, he shot them in cold blood.

617
00:45:56.629 --> 00:46:00.590
They raped and almost murdered
his daughter, Sarah.

618
00:46:00.758 --> 00:46:02.884
What if the same thing
happened to Hannah?

619
00:46:03.052 --> 00:46:06.304
Brigance! Mr. Brigance! Mr. Brigance!

620
00:46:06.472 --> 00:46:09.099
- May we ask a few questions?
- Can we get a quote?

621
00:46:09.267 --> 00:46:10.851
- Mr. Brigance.
- Excuse me a second.

622
00:46:11.018 --> 00:46:13.019
I'm going to go take a few questions.

623
00:46:13.187 --> 00:46:16.064
- Jake, this isn't the time.
- This is really good for Carl Lee.

624
00:46:16.232 --> 00:46:17.858
I'll be right back.

625
00:46:19.235 --> 00:46:20.986
Thank y'all for coming.

626
00:46:25.867 --> 00:46:29.035
I guess we'll have to read about it
in the papers.

627
00:47:26.177 --> 00:47:27.385
Praise Jesus!

628
00:47:43.110 --> 00:47:45.654
- Reverend Agee?
- Yes.

629
00:47:45.821 --> 00:47:47.322
I'm Isaiah Street.

630
00:47:47.490 --> 00:47:50.116
Well, it's an honor to meet you,
Reverend.

631
00:47:50.284 --> 00:47:52.369
I saw you march with Dr. King.

632
00:47:52.537 --> 00:47:58.542
Well, well. The struggle continues today
here in Canton.

633
00:47:59.126 --> 00:48:01.419
Carl Lee Hailey's on trial
because he's black.

634
00:48:01.587 --> 00:48:02.879
No other reason.

635
00:48:04.131 --> 00:48:07.467
- These people are with the NAACP.
- Oh?

636
00:48:07.885 --> 00:48:09.886
- Reverend Agee.
- How do you do?

637
00:48:10.054 --> 00:48:11.137
How do you do?

638
00:48:11.472 --> 00:48:17.811
Reverend Agee, the black community's
concerned that Mr. Hailey's attorney...

639
00:48:17.979 --> 00:48:20.855
is not sensitive to the needs
of the movement.

640
00:48:21.816 --> 00:48:27.195
The NAACP wishes to provide him
with a new lawyer.

641
00:48:29.323 --> 00:48:33.743
We need to raise funds
to support Carl Lee Hailey.

642
00:48:34.829 --> 00:48:37.831
I don't know, Reverend.
Time's awfully tight here.

643
00:48:39.834 --> 00:48:44.045
Obviously, we would expect you
to take...

644
00:48:44.213 --> 00:48:48.216
a modest administration fee
for your troubles.

645
00:49:14.368 --> 00:49:20.832
Your loyalty has been forged
in a baptism of fire.

646
00:49:21.959 --> 00:49:26.379
Rise, knights of the Ku Klux Klan...

647
00:49:27.006 --> 00:49:31.676
and let your brethren never regret...

648
00:49:32.720 --> 00:49:37.891
they believed you worthy of fellowship.

649
00:49:43.230 --> 00:49:45.357
Welcome to the Klan.

650
00:49:57.328 --> 00:49:59.120
I need to talk to Jake Brigance.

651
00:49:59.288 --> 00:50:01.581
He's not in. May I ask who's calling?

652
00:50:02.166 --> 00:50:05.085
Uh, well—

653
00:50:05.294 --> 00:50:06.336
Mickey Mouse.

654
00:50:06.796 --> 00:50:08.713
- Who?
- Mickey Mouse.

655
00:50:09.507 --> 00:50:11.591
Get out right now.

656
00:50:11.759 --> 00:50:12.759
Who is this?

657
00:50:12.927 --> 00:50:15.679
Get your daughter
out of the house right now.

658
00:50:16.847 --> 00:50:18.223
Mommy!

659
00:50:18.391 --> 00:50:20.433
- Hannah?
- Mommy!

660
00:50:20.601 --> 00:50:24.020
Hannah? What is it? Oh, my God!

661
00:50:24.188 --> 00:50:26.481
Max! Max, come on!

662
00:50:26.649 --> 00:50:28.024
Fire! Aah!

663
00:50:36.033 --> 00:50:39.369
It's a good thing Hastings
was nearby and got here fast.

664
00:50:39.537 --> 00:50:41.955
The whole place could've burned down.

665
00:50:42.123 --> 00:50:44.708
- Yeah, I appreciate it.
- Take care, man.

666
00:50:44.875 --> 00:50:46.835
See you in the morning.

667
00:50:53.300 --> 00:50:55.301
She asleep, baby?

668
00:50:56.637 --> 00:50:59.889
The Ku Klux Klan
is burning crosses on our lawn, Jake.

669
00:51:00.057 --> 00:51:03.143
Baby, there's been
no Klan around here for years, okay?

670
00:51:03.310 --> 00:51:07.147
This is just a couple of dorks with too much
time on their hands and too many beers.

671
00:51:11.694 --> 00:51:13.945
- I'm sorry.
- About what?

672
00:51:15.489 --> 00:51:19.117
That you weren't home when someone
practically burned our house down?

673
00:51:19.285 --> 00:51:21.911
That you missed supper
and didn't even bother to call?

674
00:51:22.079 --> 00:51:25.165
That lately you've become more
interested in getting on the news...

675
00:51:25.332 --> 00:51:27.208
than what's going on with your family?

676
00:51:27.376 --> 00:51:31.212
Or that Hannah comes home bawling
because of kids calling her a nigger-lover?

677
00:51:31.380 --> 00:51:34.466
What exactly are you sorry about, Jake?

678
00:51:42.850 --> 00:51:44.893
Remember the other night?

679
00:51:46.604 --> 00:51:49.147
I told you Carl Lee came by the office?

680
00:51:49.315 --> 00:51:51.691
Remember what we talked about then?

681
00:51:52.151 --> 00:51:54.152
About me calling Ozzie?

682
00:51:57.239 --> 00:51:59.949
You never called him, did you?

683
00:52:00.951 --> 00:52:02.410
You never called Sheriff Walls?

684
00:52:03.412 --> 00:52:05.205
I didn't call him, baby.

685
00:52:06.415 --> 00:52:10.251
Lord have mercy, Jake,
you had a responsibility.

686
00:52:10.419 --> 00:52:12.378
Carl Lee chose you.

687
00:52:12.546 --> 00:52:15.715
He told you what he was thinking.

688
00:52:15.883 --> 00:52:18.301
He told me what he was thinking,
but I didn't know—

689
00:52:18.469 --> 00:52:22.764
Jake Tyler Brigance,
we agreed, you were gonna call the sheriff.

690
00:52:22.932 --> 00:52:25.350
Now look at everything
that has happened.

691
00:52:26.060 --> 00:52:29.896
I am sorry to tell you this, darling,
but those two boys are in the ground...

692
00:52:30.064 --> 00:52:33.066
and you were in a position
to prevent every bit of this.

693
00:52:33.234 --> 00:52:34.484
Mama?

694
00:52:35.945 --> 00:52:37.487
Are you and Daddy fighting?

695
00:52:39.031 --> 00:52:42.742
No, baby. Come here.
Come here, baby. Come here.

696
00:52:43.702 --> 00:52:47.288
Mommy's just upset because
some silly man played a real bad joke, okay?

697
00:52:47.456 --> 00:52:49.415
There's nothing to worry about.

698
00:52:49.834 --> 00:52:52.877
Nothing at all, okay?

699
00:52:58.509 --> 00:53:00.510
What that Memphis doctor say about her?

700
00:53:01.762 --> 00:53:03.388
She's doing good.

701
00:53:04.390 --> 00:53:05.932
Her jaw is healing.

702
00:53:06.100 --> 00:53:09.811
She can't run and jump yet,
but it won't be long.

703
00:53:11.105 --> 00:53:12.772
How about the other?

704
00:53:20.823 --> 00:53:23.658
There was too much damage.

705
00:53:24.827 --> 00:53:26.661
She ain't gonna never have kids.

706
00:53:35.129 --> 00:53:37.463
You know, I think about them two boys.

707
00:53:37.631 --> 00:53:39.215
Dead, buried...

708
00:53:39.383 --> 00:53:41.843
probably starting to rot.

709
00:53:42.469 --> 00:53:45.305
And I remember them walking in court...

710
00:53:45.472 --> 00:53:47.390
one proud, the other scared.

711
00:53:49.018 --> 00:53:51.102
I remember how they fell.

712
00:53:51.270 --> 00:53:56.316
One on top of the other, and screaming
and squirming and not going nowhere.

713
00:53:58.193 --> 00:54:00.862
God help me, Gwen, but...

714
00:54:02.573 --> 00:54:04.866
that's the only thought
gives me comfort.

715
00:54:08.203 --> 00:54:11.289
They took up a collection for us
at church Sunday night.

716
00:54:12.041 --> 00:54:14.375
Some kind of defense fund.

717
00:54:15.127 --> 00:54:17.712
Reverend Agee gave a good service.

718
00:54:21.008 --> 00:54:27.347
We need some money around the house,
Carl Lee, for groceries and bills.

719
00:54:27.514 --> 00:54:28.806
How much you got?

720
00:54:30.517 --> 00:54:31.684
Less than 50.

721
00:54:33.687 --> 00:54:35.146
I'll think of something.

722
00:54:38.776 --> 00:54:42.695
How you think you going to get
some money while you stuck here in jail?

723
00:54:42.863 --> 00:54:44.489
Trust me, Gwen.

724
00:54:49.662 --> 00:54:51.454
I just get scared.

725
00:54:53.374 --> 00:54:55.041
Look here.

726
00:54:55.376 --> 00:55:01.172
Tell me exactly what Reverend Agee said
when he passed around the collection plate.

727
00:55:01.340 --> 00:55:04.550
I don't care.
We are dealing with life and death here.

728
00:55:04.718 --> 00:55:08.680
- I'm gonna have to talk to my supervisor.
- Well, you go talk. Get out of here.

729
00:55:08.847 --> 00:55:11.599
Morning, John.
How are things at the electric company?

730
00:55:11.767 --> 00:55:15.687
The electric company. That is the second
time this week I've had to hold him off.

731
00:55:15.854 --> 00:55:17.689
- How much do we owe?
- Two thousand dollars.

732
00:55:17.856 --> 00:55:20.817
- How much do we have?
- One hundred dollars.

733
00:55:20.985 --> 00:55:24.112
Now, look, this week nothing,
nothing has come in at all. Look.

734
00:55:24.279 --> 00:55:27.198
What about Buck Britt's retainer?
There's 2 grand.

735
00:55:27.366 --> 00:55:30.576
- That check bounced.
- What do you mean, bounced?

736
00:55:30.744 --> 00:55:32.495
It bounced, Jake.

737
00:55:32.663 --> 00:55:35.248
It's been sitting on your desk for a week.

738
00:55:35.416 --> 00:55:37.458
Not that you'd notice.

739
00:55:39.169 --> 00:55:42.672
Since you took this case, you—
You stopped talking to your clients...

740
00:55:42.840 --> 00:55:44.632
you don't take your calls, you—

741
00:55:44.800 --> 00:55:48.678
You're obsessed. That's what you are.
You're obsessed, Jake.

742
00:55:49.179 --> 00:55:52.265
- Boy, your obsession is going to break us.
- Hey, hey, hey.

743
00:55:52.433 --> 00:55:55.101
What's wrong, girl?
We've been through hard times before.

744
00:55:55.269 --> 00:55:57.186
Oh, not like this, Jake.

745
00:55:57.354 --> 00:55:59.439
Not like this.

746
00:56:00.357 --> 00:56:02.358
We've been getting calls.

747
00:56:02.526 --> 00:56:03.693
At home.

748
00:56:03.861 --> 00:56:05.069
Threats.

749
00:56:06.447 --> 00:56:10.742
You know Bud has survived two strokes.
I don't think he would survive a third.

750
00:56:10.909 --> 00:56:12.118
Why didn't you tell me?

751
00:56:13.579 --> 00:56:15.455
Why, Jake?

752
00:56:15.622 --> 00:56:16.998
Would you drop the case?

753
00:56:22.838 --> 00:56:24.047
Jake Brigance's office.

754
00:56:24.214 --> 00:56:26.799
Until they cut the phones off.

755
00:56:27.634 --> 00:56:29.093
Oh, right.

756
00:56:29.845 --> 00:56:31.054
Okay.

757
00:56:31.221 --> 00:56:34.098
Right. That was Sheriff Walls.

758
00:56:34.266 --> 00:56:36.225
You better get down to that jail.

759
00:56:43.650 --> 00:56:45.818
What's going on here, Carl Lee?

760
00:56:45.986 --> 00:56:48.071
- I'm Isaiah Street.
- Jake Brigance.

761
00:56:48.238 --> 00:56:50.406
Uh-huh. Uh...

762
00:56:50.574 --> 00:56:52.658
- I believe you know Reverend Agee.
- Jake.

763
00:56:52.826 --> 00:56:54.994
- And this is—
- Norman Reinfield.

764
00:56:55.162 --> 00:56:57.413
I've seen your picture in the paper.

765
00:56:58.290 --> 00:57:01.000
I assume these boys carry your briefcase.

766
00:57:01.168 --> 00:57:03.836
Just a small part
of my legal defense team.

767
00:57:04.004 --> 00:57:05.379
Pleasure, Mr. Brigance.

768
00:57:05.547 --> 00:57:06.672
Mm-hm.

769
00:57:06.840 --> 00:57:09.217
If this is a party, boys,
where's the chips and beer?

770
00:57:09.676 --> 00:57:13.888
Otherwise, you being here seems a bit
like illegal client solicitation.

771
00:57:14.056 --> 00:57:16.182
With Carl Lee already
having a lawyer and all.

772
00:57:16.350 --> 00:57:18.101
Well, now, just a minute, Jake.

773
00:57:18.268 --> 00:57:20.269
Carl Lee invited us here.

774
00:57:22.481 --> 00:57:24.357
Mr. Brigance...

775
00:57:24.525 --> 00:57:26.818
let me be frank.

776
00:57:26.985 --> 00:57:30.363
Mr. Hailey's case
has far-reaching ramifications.

777
00:57:30.864 --> 00:57:33.199
Carl Lee's acquittal
for the killings of two white men...

778
00:57:33.367 --> 00:57:35.701
would do more
for black people in Mississippi...

779
00:57:35.869 --> 00:57:39.247
than any event since
we integrated the schools.

780
00:57:39.414 --> 00:57:42.583
His conviction, on the other hand,
will be a slap at us.

781
00:57:42.751 --> 00:57:44.877
A symbol of deep-seated racism.

782
00:57:45.045 --> 00:57:47.296
Perhaps enough to ignite a nation.

783
00:57:47.714 --> 00:57:49.882
See how important this case is?

784
00:57:50.050 --> 00:57:52.593
Enter Mr. Reinfield's death squad, right?

785
00:57:52.761 --> 00:57:56.639
It's an unfortunate nickname,
but apropos.

786
00:57:56.807 --> 00:58:00.226
My lawyers and I handle
only capital-murder cases, Mr. Hailey.

787
00:58:00.394 --> 00:58:03.729
Yeah, and of all your cases, Norman,
how many are supposed to be lost...

788
00:58:03.897 --> 00:58:06.524
- ... so you can martyr the victim?
- Now, Mr. Brigance.

789
00:58:06.692 --> 00:58:11.571
How much a defense like that cost?

790
00:58:12.614 --> 00:58:14.157
Yeah.

791
00:58:15.033 --> 00:58:16.617
Would you say about 100,000?

792
00:58:16.785 --> 00:58:20.830
We are prepared to accept
7000 in litigation expenses.

793
00:58:20.998 --> 00:58:24.750
Well, Carl Lee doesn't have $7000.

794
00:58:24.918 --> 00:58:25.960
Do you, Carl Lee?

795
00:58:26.503 --> 00:58:32.091
The NAACP has raised $5000
for Carl Lee's legal defense fund.

796
00:58:32.259 --> 00:58:35.428
And we raised an additional
$2000 from the local churches.

797
00:58:35.596 --> 00:58:37.263
Let me ask you something, Reverend.

798
00:58:37.681 --> 00:58:40.641
How much of that cash
you offer my wife and kids?

799
00:58:40.809 --> 00:58:44.896
Well, that money is to go to pay
for lawyers' fees and stuff like that.

800
00:58:45.063 --> 00:58:47.190
That ain't what you told the church,
now, is it?

801
00:58:47.983 --> 00:58:49.859
You almost cried when you told them...

802
00:58:50.027 --> 00:58:54.238
how my family might starve if they
didn't donate all they could, didn't you?

803
00:58:54.948 --> 00:58:57.658
Well, the money is for you
and your family, Carl Lee...

804
00:58:57.826 --> 00:59:00.786
but we thought it'd be better spent
on your legal defense.

805
00:59:00.954 --> 00:59:03.623
Well, speaking of that defense fund...

806
00:59:03.790 --> 00:59:06.292
can I use that for any lawyer I want?

807
00:59:06.460 --> 00:59:09.295
Well, it's not that simple, Carl Lee.

808
00:59:09.463 --> 00:59:12.340
Actually, it is that simple, Carl Lee.

809
00:59:12.507 --> 00:59:17.220
Unless the NAACP wants to go on record
as soliciting funds under false pretenses.

810
00:59:17.387 --> 00:59:20.598
Listen, Carl Lee, we raised that money...

811
00:59:20.766 --> 00:59:23.809
for these men to get you out of here,
not for this cracker to—

812
00:59:23.977 --> 00:59:27.855
Now, hey, hey, hey.
Hold on. Hold on right there, now.

813
00:59:28.315 --> 00:59:31.901
Let me just get this straight here,
Reverend.

814
00:59:34.488 --> 00:59:37.907
If you don't give my wife that cash...

815
00:59:38.075 --> 00:59:41.953
I'm gonna see to it everybody in this
town knows you're a lying crook.

816
00:59:42.621 --> 00:59:45.164
I'm sure your congregation
will be interested to know...

817
00:59:45.332 --> 00:59:48.542
Gwen and the kids can't eat
because you want in with the NAACP.

818
00:59:48.710 --> 00:59:51.963
That's right.
By the time I get through with you...

819
00:59:52.130 --> 00:59:56.008
you won't be able to collect 2 cents
in that collection plate on Sunday.

820
00:59:56.176 --> 01:00:00.346
We'll expect the check for the Hailey family
this afternoon, Reverend Agee.

821
01:00:01.306 --> 01:00:04.684
Reverend Street,
I sure do appreciate your fine work...

822
01:00:04.851 --> 01:00:07.061
but I'm gonna take my chances
with Jake here.

823
01:00:09.231 --> 01:00:11.482
Thanks for coming down, Mr. Reinfield.

824
01:00:12.317 --> 01:00:15.820
Uh, and we'll be expecting that check
for Jake's legal services...

825
01:00:15.988 --> 01:00:17.989
around the same time this afternoon.

826
01:00:22.119 --> 01:00:23.828
Good day, men.

827
01:00:30.627 --> 01:00:32.378
Go.

828
01:00:35.882 --> 01:00:37.383
Go.

829
01:00:38.093 --> 01:00:39.677
Good.

830
01:00:41.972 --> 01:00:44.056
You set that whole thing up, didn't you?

831
01:00:44.224 --> 01:00:46.100
Couldn't have did it without you, Jake.

832
01:00:48.645 --> 01:00:50.521
Make one hell of a team, Carl Lee.

833
01:00:51.315 --> 01:00:54.400
You out there, Jake. I'm in here.

834
01:00:54.568 --> 01:00:55.901
We ain't no team.

835
01:01:20.594 --> 01:01:22.219
There's trouble.

836
01:01:23.764 --> 01:01:25.598
Oh, lookie there.

837
01:01:30.854 --> 01:01:32.646
No, here's trouble, Harry Rex.

838
01:01:41.406 --> 01:01:43.157
Hi. You are...?

839
01:01:43.325 --> 01:01:45.034
Roark, meet Mr. Harry Rex Vonner...

840
01:01:45.202 --> 01:01:48.788
the most effective, connected,
morally compromised lawyer in the country.

841
01:01:48.955 --> 01:01:52.249
- Oh. Ellen Roark, brilliant law student.
- Do with me as you will.

842
01:01:52.417 --> 01:01:54.460
- Looking forward to it.
- Okay.

843
01:01:54.961 --> 01:01:57.797
Um, well,
thought this might interest you.

844
01:01:57.964 --> 01:02:02.343
In all murder trials, it seems the insanity
plea only makes up 1 percent overall.

845
01:02:02.511 --> 01:02:05.179
And of the 1 percent of that
that resulted in acquittal...

846
01:02:05.347 --> 01:02:07.306
success rested almost wholly on the—

847
01:02:07.474 --> 01:02:11.852
On the defending psychiatrist regardless of
the quality of the psychological testimony.

848
01:02:12.020 --> 01:02:13.562
- Yeah.
- Shazam.

849
01:02:13.730 --> 01:02:14.772
She is brilliant.

850
01:02:14.940 --> 01:02:17.024
"She." That would be me?

851
01:02:17.192 --> 01:02:19.485
- Now, who else would she be?
- So she would be me.

852
01:02:19.653 --> 01:02:22.363
She is saying that
if I take this plea to trial...

853
01:02:22.531 --> 01:02:26.158
the verdict is going to hinge on whose
shrink the jury finds more credible.

854
01:02:26.660 --> 01:02:28.077
She would be correct.

855
01:02:28.662 --> 01:02:30.079
She would.

856
01:02:30.789 --> 01:02:32.706
So are you sure you don't need any help?

857
01:02:32.874 --> 01:02:36.335
I do. I'm hiring. Right now. Me.

858
01:02:36.837 --> 01:02:40.923
Roark, I am sure that I don't need any help.
Thank you, though.

859
01:02:41.091 --> 01:02:43.008
Okay.

860
01:02:43.176 --> 01:02:46.429
I guess that would just have
to be your loss, then, huh?

861
01:02:48.223 --> 01:02:50.599
Nice to meet you, Morally Compromised.

862
01:02:50.767 --> 01:02:51.976
Pleasure's all mine.

863
01:02:52.144 --> 01:02:53.686
She.

864
01:02:57.149 --> 01:03:00.609
Got to love the Lord
for making things like that.

865
01:03:00.777 --> 01:03:03.362
Sure you don't wanna at least
take a peak at her résumé?

866
01:03:03.530 --> 01:03:05.823
Not like you couldn't use the help.

867
01:03:05.991 --> 01:03:10.035
No, I don't want to look at her résumé,
Harry Rex, because I have you.

868
01:03:10.203 --> 01:03:12.288
- You do?
- Yeah, buddy.

869
01:03:12.456 --> 01:03:15.833
This is your chance to put aside
your shady sources, back-alley deals...

870
01:03:16.001 --> 01:03:19.545
your greedy divorcées,
and do some real law for a change.

871
01:03:21.339 --> 01:03:23.090
Mr. Vonner, in short...

872
01:03:23.258 --> 01:03:26.886
you now have the opportunity
to work on a case that matters.

873
01:03:27.721 --> 01:03:29.096
Let me get this straight.

874
01:03:29.264 --> 01:03:33.893
You want me to put aside my empty,
soulless, shady...

875
01:03:34.060 --> 01:03:36.687
astonishingly lucrative,
divorcée practice...

876
01:03:36.855 --> 01:03:40.900
come work with you on an unwinnable,
bleeding-heart, lose-all-my-friends...

877
01:03:41.067 --> 01:03:43.569
straight-to-the-gas-chamber case
because it matters?

878
01:03:43.737 --> 01:03:45.070
That is a novel idea, I know.

879
01:03:45.238 --> 01:03:47.490
No way, never,
presumptuous little shit.

880
01:03:50.243 --> 01:03:51.577
Good night, y'all.

881
01:03:56.500 --> 01:03:58.709
- Hello?
- I need the sheriff.

882
01:03:58.877 --> 01:04:02.213
- He's sleeping now.
- Well, get him up.

883
01:04:02.380 --> 01:04:06.091
- Who is this?
- Someone's gonna die tonight.

884
01:04:28.698 --> 01:04:30.991
- Unh!
- I got him!

885
01:04:31.826 --> 01:04:34.119
- Get his ass, Ozzie!
- What's in the case?

886
01:04:44.339 --> 01:04:46.590
- This thing's ticking.
- What's in the case?

887
01:04:46.800 --> 01:04:49.093
I ain't saying, nigger.

888
01:04:53.098 --> 01:04:55.182
- Family out of the house?
- Yeah.

889
01:04:57.018 --> 01:04:58.269
It's locked.

890
01:05:03.191 --> 01:05:04.483
Now I want you to open that.

891
01:05:17.330 --> 01:05:18.372
Oh, man...

892
01:05:20.750 --> 01:05:21.792
Defuse it.

893
01:05:22.335 --> 01:05:26.839
I'm gonna take you
and this nigger-lover to hell with—

894
01:05:28.008 --> 01:05:31.176
Ain't nothing more dangerous
in this world than a fool with a cause.

895
01:05:31.344 --> 01:05:34.263
Lay that thing back down there.
Let's get the hell out of here.

896
01:05:34.431 --> 01:05:36.682
Carla loves this house.

897
01:05:55.869 --> 01:05:58.537
- How you doing, Stan?
- Hey, how you doing?

898
01:05:59.456 --> 01:06:00.497
Come here, girl.

899
01:06:01.708 --> 01:06:03.584
Mwah.

900
01:06:04.336 --> 01:06:06.712
Daddy, are you coming to Grandpa's too?

901
01:06:06.880 --> 01:06:09.882
Mm-mm. Not this time, baby.
Daddy's gotta stay here and work.

902
01:06:10.050 --> 01:06:11.967
You and your mama
have a good time, okay?

903
01:06:12.135 --> 01:06:14.595
- All right.
- All right. You be good.

904
01:06:14.929 --> 01:06:16.263
Go get your stuff down there.

905
01:06:17.515 --> 01:06:19.808
You said you'd withdraw
if it got too dangerous.

906
01:06:19.976 --> 01:06:21.060
I know.

907
01:06:21.227 --> 01:06:23.771
But I can't quit now, you know that.

908
01:06:24.314 --> 01:06:27.941
Carl Lee Hailey's facing the gas chamber,
baby. The man is counting on me.

909
01:06:28.985 --> 01:06:31.195
I understand that, Jake.

910
01:06:31.363 --> 01:06:33.864
I want you to remember
that we're counting on you too.

911
01:06:34.032 --> 01:06:36.367
What if something happens to you?

912
01:06:36.534 --> 01:06:39.411
Nothing's gonna happen to me, baby.
Come here.

913
01:06:39.871 --> 01:06:41.580
Give me a hug? Hmm?

914
01:06:42.290 --> 01:06:43.791
Everything's gonna be all right.

915
01:06:43.958 --> 01:06:46.669
I'm gonna be fine,
you're gonna be fine. Okay?

916
01:06:46.836 --> 01:06:48.504
Okay, babe?

917
01:06:49.714 --> 01:06:50.756
I promise.

918
01:06:53.051 --> 01:06:56.261
Watch you don't make your wife promises
you can't keep.

919
01:06:58.765 --> 01:07:00.099
Hannah?

920
01:07:00.266 --> 01:07:01.934
- You ready?
- Uh-huh.

921
01:07:02.102 --> 01:07:04.645
Last boarding call.

922
01:07:14.614 --> 01:07:16.073
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

923
01:07:16.241 --> 01:07:17.950
Come in.

924
01:07:18.493 --> 01:07:19.952
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

925
01:07:20.120 --> 01:07:22.538
You may come this way.
The judge is upstairs.

926
01:07:22.706 --> 01:07:24.373
Thank you, sir.

927
01:07:32.882 --> 01:07:34.466
Judge Noose.

928
01:07:35.635 --> 01:07:37.636
Thanks for coming.

929
01:07:39.097 --> 01:07:41.849
- Heard you had a little trouble last night.
- Yes, sir.

930
01:07:42.016 --> 01:07:45.060
Makes you wonder about
the sensibleness of taking this case.

931
01:07:45.228 --> 01:07:48.439
This is a beautiful place
you have here, judge.

932
01:07:48.606 --> 01:07:50.149
I'll get to the point.

933
01:07:50.316 --> 01:07:56.155
I've thoroughly reviewed
your brief request in that change of venue.

934
01:07:56.322 --> 01:08:01.410
And I agree with you. I think it's impossible
to find a fair and impartial jury in Canton.

935
01:08:01.578 --> 01:08:06.498
In fact, I think it's impossible to find a fair
and impartial jury anywhere in Mississippi.

936
01:08:06.666 --> 01:08:08.041
And as such...

937
01:08:08.209 --> 01:08:10.627
a jury here would be...

938
01:08:10.795 --> 01:08:13.756
as fair as a jury anywhere else.

939
01:08:13.923 --> 01:08:18.343
So I've decided to deny your request
for a change of venue.

940
01:08:20.013 --> 01:08:21.638
Well, I guess that...

941
01:08:21.806 --> 01:08:23.390
gives me something to appeal.

942
01:08:23.558 --> 01:08:26.185
Uh, actually, no.

943
01:08:26.352 --> 01:08:28.687
I spoke to Judge Dent...

944
01:08:28.855 --> 01:08:33.025
and he led me to believe that the
supreme court would uphold my ruling.

945
01:08:34.360 --> 01:08:36.445
You certainly have
covered your bases, judge.

946
01:08:38.406 --> 01:08:42.117
Jake, you're a good lawyer.

947
01:08:42.786 --> 01:08:46.330
You're bright and ambitious. Talented.
You could be somebody around here.

948
01:08:46.498 --> 01:08:50.584
You sure you wanna be known
as the man that defended that murderer?

949
01:08:51.127 --> 01:08:53.587
Could be very unpopular.

950
01:08:54.339 --> 01:08:56.215
Talk to your client.

951
01:08:56.841 --> 01:08:58.217
He pleads guilty...

952
01:08:58.384 --> 01:09:00.928
I'll recommend Buckley
accept a plea of manslaughter.

953
01:09:01.095 --> 01:09:02.346
He'd be out in 20.

954
01:09:03.139 --> 01:09:06.099
Yeah. And how's his wife supposed
to raise his family alone?

955
01:09:06.935 --> 01:09:08.602
Better than being a widow.

956
01:09:10.605 --> 01:09:12.231
Think about it.

957
01:09:12.398 --> 01:09:16.276
Why toss away a promising career, hmm?

958
01:09:19.113 --> 01:09:21.657
- Good day, judge.
- Thanks for coming.

959
01:09:26.246 --> 01:09:29.832
All right, Lucien.
Where the hell is this guy?

960
01:09:29.999 --> 01:09:31.917
Born alcoholic.

961
01:09:32.085 --> 01:09:34.670
But the man cannot hold his liquor.

962
01:09:34.838 --> 01:09:40.759
Jake, allow me to present
Dr. Willard Tyrell Bass.

963
01:09:40.927 --> 01:09:43.262
Expert witness for the defense.

964
01:09:43.429 --> 01:09:48.183
W.T., this is Jake Brigance, my protégé.

965
01:09:52.772 --> 01:09:54.606
Dr. Bass.

966
01:09:58.903 --> 01:10:01.738
- Are you kidding me?
- No, relax.

967
01:10:01.906 --> 01:10:04.408
When he's sober, he's terrific.

968
01:10:05.285 --> 01:10:09.746
He has his license,
his credentials are impeccable.

969
01:10:13.585 --> 01:10:16.003
- Well?
- I need a drink.

970
01:10:16.170 --> 01:10:17.963
Three in the afternoon?

971
01:10:18.131 --> 01:10:21.925
- My, oh, my. What would your wife say?
- I am my own man, Lucien.

972
01:10:22.093 --> 01:10:24.469
- I drink when I want.
- When did she leave town?

973
01:10:24.637 --> 01:10:26.889
- This morning.
- Ha-ha-ha.

974
01:10:45.700 --> 01:10:47.326
God! Unh!

975
01:10:51.748 --> 01:10:52.915
Bud?

976
01:10:59.505 --> 01:11:01.048
Oh, my—

977
01:11:02.300 --> 01:11:03.342
That's enough.

978
01:11:09.807 --> 01:11:11.516
Now, you tell your boss...

979
01:11:11.684 --> 01:11:14.603
next time people are gonna die.

980
01:11:18.358 --> 01:11:20.067
Oh, Bud.

981
01:11:21.152 --> 01:11:23.070
Oh, Bud.

982
01:11:46.719 --> 01:11:48.261
Hi.

983
01:11:48.429 --> 01:11:49.471
Morning.

984
01:11:53.226 --> 01:11:55.227
Nice parking job. Late night?

985
01:12:02.235 --> 01:12:04.820
- Yeah.
