1224
01:28:41.984 --> 01:28:44.318
Move, move, move.

1225
01:29:22.107 --> 01:29:23.691
Hey, buddy.

1226
01:29:24.818 --> 01:29:26.152
Seen my dog?

1227
01:29:26.611 --> 01:29:28.070
Looking for my dog.

1228
01:29:28.238 --> 01:29:32.199
Max, come here, boy! Let's go!
Come on, Max!

1229
01:29:33.952 --> 01:29:39.832
I booked you on the 9:15 to Gulfport.
Economy, of course.

1230
01:29:40.125 --> 01:29:41.834
Go see your wife and daughter, Jake.

1231
01:29:44.087 --> 01:29:46.505
What'd you do that for, Harry Rex?

1232
01:29:46.715 --> 01:29:48.632
We got trial in less than three hours.

1233
01:29:48.967 --> 01:29:50.009
Oh, come on.

1234
01:29:50.177 --> 01:29:52.553
Noose would give you a continuance
in a flash.

1235
01:29:52.721 --> 01:29:56.682
NAACP boys be down here before lunch.
Drooling.

1236
01:29:57.434 --> 01:30:00.478
Max, let's go, boy! Come on!

1237
01:30:01.354 --> 01:30:03.189
Jake, listen to me.

1238
01:30:03.732 --> 01:30:07.068
Your marriage is on the rocks,
you're about to have an affair.

1239
01:30:07.235 --> 01:30:10.738
Your career's in ruins if you're lucky,
and if you're not, you're dead.

1240
01:30:12.282 --> 01:30:13.783
Don't get me wrong, my friend.

1241
01:30:14.743 --> 01:30:17.661
What you've put into this case,
you even inspired me, and I'm—

1242
01:30:17.829 --> 01:30:19.872
I'm uninspirable.

1243
01:30:20.040 --> 01:30:21.749
Do everyone a favor, though.

1244
01:30:21.917 --> 01:30:24.001
Drop the case.

1245
01:30:27.339 --> 01:30:29.673
No, I can't.

1246
01:30:30.300 --> 01:30:32.843
I won't. I'm not gonna quit.

1247
01:30:33.804 --> 01:30:36.263
I quit now, and all this is for nothing. No.

1248
01:30:39.851 --> 01:30:42.603
Max, come on now.
Max, where are you? Come on, Max!

1249
01:30:42.771 --> 01:30:45.147
Max is dead, and you're next.

1250
01:30:46.233 --> 01:30:48.109
Walk away.

1251
01:30:57.869 --> 01:31:00.496
Max. Come here, boy.

1252
01:31:01.373 --> 01:31:03.290
Come here. Come here, boy. Ha-ha-ha.

1253
01:31:03.500 --> 01:31:05.000
Come here. Come here.

1254
01:31:05.168 --> 01:31:07.378
Who's got the goods, huh? Huh?

1255
01:31:09.923 --> 01:31:12.550
Pretrial strategy at my office
in less than two hours...

1256
01:31:12.717 --> 01:31:15.386
and I expect to see your ass there.

1257
01:31:15.762 --> 01:31:18.681
Free Carl Lee!
Free Carl Lee! Free Carl Lee!

1258
01:31:18.849 --> 01:31:22.184
Free Carl Lee! Free Carl Lee!
Free Carl Lee!

1259
01:31:30.152 --> 01:31:32.153
Fry Carl Lee.

1260
01:31:33.530 --> 01:31:34.780
Free Carl Lee!

1261
01:31:36.491 --> 01:31:38.868
Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee!

1262
01:31:39.035 --> 01:31:40.244
Free Carl Lee!

1263
01:31:43.165 --> 01:31:45.499
Free Carl Lee! Free Carl Lee!

1264
01:31:49.546 --> 01:31:53.174
Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee!

1265
01:31:53.341 --> 01:31:57.803
Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee!

1266
01:32:05.020 --> 01:32:08.397
Now, Mr. Buckley, you may begin.

1267
01:32:08.565 --> 01:32:10.441
Thank you, Your Honor.

1268
01:32:13.278 --> 01:32:15.905
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

1269
01:32:17.824 --> 01:32:22.494
You are Cora Mae Cobb, the mother of
Billy Ray Cobb the deceased, are you not?

1270
01:32:22.662 --> 01:32:24.121
Yes, sir.

1271
01:32:24.289 --> 01:32:26.707
And where were you
when your son was murdered?

1272
01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:30.211
I was right outside that door right there.

1273
01:32:30.378 --> 01:32:33.172
Me and Freddie was waiting
for his hearing.

1274
01:32:33.673 --> 01:32:35.674
He was walking up the stairs...

1275
01:32:35.842 --> 01:32:37.635
in handcuffs.

1276
01:32:37.928 --> 01:32:41.513
Can you tell us how old your son was
at the time of his death?

1277
01:32:42.891 --> 01:32:43.974
Twenty-three.

1278
01:32:45.852 --> 01:32:48.020
You say your son was 23 when he died?

1279
01:32:48.438 --> 01:32:49.480
Yes.

1280
01:32:49.648 --> 01:32:52.566
In those 23 years, Mrs. Cobb...

1281
01:32:52.734 --> 01:32:54.860
how many other children
did your son kidnap?

1282
01:32:55.028 --> 01:32:56.820
Objection, Your Honor! Objection!

1283
01:32:56.988 --> 01:33:00.616
Sustained. You—
You are out of order, Mr. Brigance.

1284
01:33:00.784 --> 01:33:03.452
- Withdraw the question.
- The jury will disregard...

1285
01:33:03.620 --> 01:33:05.788
the last question from Mr. Brigance.

1286
01:33:06.665 --> 01:33:10.084
Mrs. Cobb, in your son's 23 years...

1287
01:33:10.252 --> 01:33:12.294
how many other children did he rape?

1288
01:33:12.462 --> 01:33:15.089
Mr. Brigance. In my chambers.

1289
01:33:16.174 --> 01:33:17.508
Court will recess for lunch.

1290
01:33:20.345 --> 01:33:22.930
I don't get it.
Why is he antagonizing the judge?

1291
01:33:23.098 --> 01:33:25.349
He should've known
Noose'd pull him into chambers.

1292
01:33:25.517 --> 01:33:29.770
Of course he knew. Jake got to draw first
blood and he knows that's more important.

1293
01:33:30.897 --> 01:33:32.773
- Hello, Harry.
- Hi, Rufie.

1294
01:33:32.941 --> 01:33:36.819
- Sweetheart, come play on a winning team.
- How's that impotence thing, Rufus?

1295
01:33:40.240 --> 01:33:43.033
You're not being paid
for the work you're doing, are you?

1296
01:33:43.201 --> 01:33:44.285
No, sir.

1297
01:33:45.704 --> 01:33:48.122
Well, I guess Jake's paying you
in other ways, then, isn't he?

1298
01:33:50.292 --> 01:33:51.375
Impotence?

1299
01:33:51.543 --> 01:33:53.168
Yep. Girls talk.

1300
01:33:53.336 --> 01:33:58.173
Sheriff, if you would,
will you please identify this weapon?

1301
01:33:58.341 --> 01:33:59.925
It's the weapon found
at the scene.

1302
01:34:00.635 --> 01:34:04.638
And were you able to identify
any of the fingerprints found on this gun?

1303
01:34:04.889 --> 01:34:08.100
Yes. The prints on the gun
matched those of Carl Lee Hailey.

1304
01:34:08.268 --> 01:34:09.727
You're sure?

1305
01:34:10.228 --> 01:34:11.562
Yes.

1306
01:34:11.730 --> 01:34:15.941
Your Honor, I'd like to enter this
into evidence as Exhibit S18.

1307
01:34:16.109 --> 01:34:18.360
We have no further use of this witness.

1308
01:34:22.490 --> 01:34:24.491
Sheriff Walls.

1309
01:34:25.869 --> 01:34:27.786
Did you arrest Cobb and Willard?

1310
01:34:27.954 --> 01:34:29.455
Yes, I did.

1311
01:34:29.622 --> 01:34:31.665
I arrested them for the rape...

1312
01:34:31.833 --> 01:34:35.753
and attempted murder
of 10-year-old Tonya Hailey.

1313
01:34:35.920 --> 01:34:37.546
And is it true that Pete Willard...

1314
01:34:37.714 --> 01:34:39.506
signed a written confession...

1315
01:34:39.674 --> 01:34:43.344
saying that he and Billy Ray Cobb
did rape Tonya Hailey?

1316
01:34:43.511 --> 01:34:46.430
Objection. That's inadmissible,
and Mr. Brigance knows it.

1317
01:34:46.598 --> 01:34:49.433
Mr. Brigance,
I've spoken to you before.

1318
01:34:49.601 --> 01:34:52.436
We are not trying the rape
of Miss Hailey today...

1319
01:34:52.604 --> 01:34:57.274
but the murder of two young men,
and if you continue in this performance...

1320
01:34:58.109 --> 01:34:59.735
I'll hold you in contempt.

1321
01:34:59.986 --> 01:35:01.487
Now, is that understood?

1322
01:35:02.489 --> 01:35:04.031
Yes, sir.

1323
01:35:05.367 --> 01:35:07.618
I have no further questions,
Your Honor.

1324
01:35:07.786 --> 01:35:09.453
Yes.

1325
01:35:10.622 --> 01:35:12.581
You say something, sheriff?

1326
01:35:14.459 --> 01:35:17.628
- Yes, he did sign a confession.
- Objection, Your Honor!

1327
01:35:18.046 --> 01:35:23.050
Jurors, you will disregard
the last remark of Sheriff Walls.

1328
01:35:23.218 --> 01:35:27.179
Court is adjourned
till tomorrow morning 9:00.

1329
01:35:48.159 --> 01:35:50.369
I'm taking Bud back to Oxford.

1330
01:35:51.955 --> 01:35:54.248
He always missed Oxford.

1331
01:36:11.141 --> 01:36:13.600
I don't know what to say,
Ethel, I don't know.

1332
01:36:13.768 --> 01:36:16.270
There's nothing you can say.

1333
01:36:17.522 --> 01:36:20.691
I know you didn't want
any of this to happen...

1334
01:36:20.859 --> 01:36:22.776
but it happened all the same.

1335
01:36:24.696 --> 01:36:28.115
You wagered all our lives on this.

1336
01:36:28.575 --> 01:36:33.203
You just went ahead and did what you
felt you had to do, no matter what the cost.

1337
01:36:35.540 --> 01:36:38.500
Some folks think that's brave.

1338
01:36:39.377 --> 01:36:41.503
Not me, Jake.

1339
01:36:42.422 --> 01:36:44.339
Now, you may win...

1340
01:36:44.966 --> 01:36:47.843
but I think we've all lost here.

1341
01:36:54.559 --> 01:37:00.397
- Would you help an old lady to her car?
- You don't need any help, Ethel...

1342
01:37:00.565 --> 01:37:05.027
but it would be my honor
to escort you to your automobile.

1343
01:37:19.501 --> 01:37:21.460
Didn't like that one?

1344
01:37:21.878 --> 01:37:23.837
Buckley is presenting
his shrink tomorrow.

1345
01:37:24.005 --> 01:37:27.132
I can't come up with one way
to bring him down. Not one.

1346
01:37:27.300 --> 01:37:31.553
I keep asking myself, "What would
Jake do? What would my father do?

1347
01:37:31.721 --> 01:37:32.763
What would Lucien do?"

1348
01:37:32.931 --> 01:37:35.224
That's your problem right there.

1349
01:37:35.391 --> 01:37:39.269
What you gotta ask yourself is,
"What would Harry Rex do?"

1350
01:37:39.437 --> 01:37:41.021
What would Harry Rex do?

1351
01:37:41.189 --> 01:37:42.523
Cheat.

1352
01:37:42.690 --> 01:37:44.107
Cheat like crazy.

1353
01:37:48.613 --> 01:37:49.613
Yeah. Yeah, I did.

1354
01:37:49.781 --> 01:37:52.616
I'll bring her around the side.

1355
01:37:55.370 --> 01:37:56.703
Uh-huh.

1356
01:37:56.871 --> 01:37:58.372
- Hey, Cheryl.
- Hi.

1357
01:38:00.166 --> 01:38:01.667
So we gotta talk about it.

1358
01:38:02.252 --> 01:38:03.544
Now, wait a minute.

1359
01:38:03.711 --> 01:38:06.588
The judge said absolutely
not to discuss this case.

1360
01:38:06.756 --> 01:38:09.299
That judge ain't stuck here
away from his wife and kids.

1361
01:38:09.467 --> 01:38:13.345
The sooner we start talking about it,
the sooner we can get home.

1362
01:38:13.513 --> 01:38:15.973
I wanna get out of here
just as much as anybody else.

1363
01:38:16.140 --> 01:38:17.975
Let's get on with it.

1364
01:38:19.978 --> 01:38:21.395
Undecided?

1365
01:38:24.732 --> 01:38:26.233
Four.

1366
01:38:26.401 --> 01:38:28.277
Guilty?

1367
01:38:32.991 --> 01:38:34.825
Seven.

1368
01:38:35.493 --> 01:38:36.535
Not guilty?

1369
01:38:41.165 --> 01:38:43.500
That nigger's dead, y'all.

1370
01:39:01.686 --> 01:39:05.188
I know, I know. Folks in town
just can't get enough of this trial.

1371
01:39:05.356 --> 01:39:09.526
And that's why my editor said I needed
to come down and interview Rodeheaver.

1372
01:39:10.069 --> 01:39:12.446
I'm afraid
Dr. Rodeheaver's in court today.

1373
01:39:12.989 --> 01:39:14.031
Oh.

1374
01:39:14.574 --> 01:39:17.034
If a pretty girl like you
wants to be a reporter...

1375
01:39:17.201 --> 01:39:19.202
maybe she should do
some better research?

1376
01:39:19.370 --> 01:39:20.412
Yeah. Ha.

1377
01:39:20.580 --> 01:39:23.874
Well, um, you know what?
I don't— I don't mind waiting...

1378
01:39:24.042 --> 01:39:26.543
because my paper really wants
this interview...

1379
01:39:26.711 --> 01:39:28.962
so is he still in Room 369?
I'll just go there.

1380
01:39:29.130 --> 01:39:33.342
No, dear. Wrong again. He's in 128.
But he's gone all day.

1381
01:39:33.509 --> 01:39:35.010
You can't see him today.

1382
01:39:35.178 --> 01:39:38.889
You wanna come back to my office
and we can schedule an appointment?

1383
01:39:39.057 --> 01:39:41.183
You know what?
I'll come back another time...

1384
01:39:41.351 --> 01:39:44.102
when he's got time to talk,
when things kind of die down.

1385
01:39:44.270 --> 01:39:46.813
- I appreciate it. Thank you.
- You can call me any time.

1386
01:39:46.981 --> 01:39:48.815
Okay. Bye-bye.

1387
01:39:52.070 --> 01:39:55.822
Your Honor,
the state calls Deputy Dwayne Looney.

1388
01:40:31.776 --> 01:40:33.276
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

1389
01:40:33.444 --> 01:40:36.405
Would you please state
your name for the record?

1390
01:40:36.572 --> 01:40:39.783
Deputy Dwayne Powell Looney.

1391
01:40:39.951 --> 01:40:41.743
Thank you, Deputy Looney.

1392
01:40:41.911 --> 01:40:44.538
You were present at the murders
of Billy Ray Cobb...

1393
01:40:44.706 --> 01:40:46.957
and James Lewis Willard,
were you not?

1394
01:40:47.125 --> 01:40:48.709
Yes, sir. I was.

1395
01:40:48.876 --> 01:40:50.752
If you can remember...

1396
01:40:50.920 --> 01:40:55.132
describe how you were wounded
for the members of the jury.

1397
01:40:55.299 --> 01:40:58.802
I think bullets bounced off the floor,
caught me in the knee.

1398
01:40:58.970 --> 01:41:00.887
And what happened to your leg?

1399
01:41:02.265 --> 01:41:03.557
Doc cut it off.

1400
01:41:04.892 --> 01:41:09.938
And after the loss of your right leg,
Detective Looney...

1401
01:41:10.898 --> 01:41:13.275
are you still able
to serve as a police officer?

1402
01:41:15.194 --> 01:41:17.529
I'm able to perform...

1403
01:41:21.159 --> 01:41:24.661
I'm able to perform a number of services.

1404
01:41:24.829 --> 01:41:27.456
Did you get a good look at the man
with the gun?

1405
01:41:27.623 --> 01:41:28.665
No, sir.

1406
01:41:29.667 --> 01:41:34.838
However, Mr. Hailey did personally
apologize for his shooting me.

1407
01:41:36.966 --> 01:41:38.383
Oh.

1408
01:41:40.136 --> 01:41:43.305
So Mr. Hailey admitted shooting you.

1409
01:41:43.890 --> 01:41:44.931
Yes, sir.

1410
01:41:45.099 --> 01:41:46.975
I have no further questions, Your Honor.

1411
01:41:47.143 --> 01:41:49.060
- Mr. Brigance.
- No questions, Your Honor.

1412
01:41:49.228 --> 01:41:50.687
Wait a minute.

1413
01:41:50.855 --> 01:41:53.356
- Uh, Mr. Buckley?
- Yes, Your Honor.

1414
01:41:53.524 --> 01:41:54.900
The state would like to call—

1415
01:41:55.067 --> 01:41:57.027
Give me a moment
to speak with my client.

1416
01:41:57.195 --> 01:41:58.361
Take your time.

1417
01:42:00.323 --> 01:42:02.574
Ask him if he thinks I ought to go to jail.

1418
01:42:02.867 --> 01:42:05.827
Carl Lee, they amputated his leg
because you shot him.

1419
01:42:05.995 --> 01:42:07.788
He's a witness for the prosecution.

1420
01:42:07.955 --> 01:42:10.040
- You're my lawyer, ain't you?
- Yeah.

1421
01:42:10.583 --> 01:42:12.459
Ask him.

1422
01:42:18.758 --> 01:42:22.886
- Your Honor, one question.
- Make up your mind, Mr. Brigance.

1423
01:42:27.141 --> 01:42:28.183
Deputy Looney.

1424
01:42:29.769 --> 01:42:32.896
Do you think Carl Lee
shooting you was intentional?

1425
01:42:33.064 --> 01:42:34.481
No, sir.

1426
01:42:34.649 --> 01:42:35.982
It was an accident.

1427
01:42:40.404 --> 01:42:41.446
Ask him.

1428
01:42:48.538 --> 01:42:51.498
Do you think he should be punished
for shooting you?

1429
01:42:52.291 --> 01:42:54.042
No, sir.

1430
01:42:54.210 --> 01:42:57.838
I hold no ill will toward the man.

1431
01:42:58.256 --> 01:43:00.090
He did what I would've done.

1432
01:43:00.258 --> 01:43:02.175
What do you mean by that,
Deputy Looney?

1433
01:43:02.343 --> 01:43:04.803
I mean I don't blame him
for what he did.

1434
01:43:04.971 --> 01:43:06.805
Those boys raped his little girl.

1435
01:43:06.973 --> 01:43:11.476
Objection, Your Honor. The witness's
opinion on this matter is irrelevant.

1436
01:43:11.644 --> 01:43:17.357
Your Honor, I believe Deputy Looney
has earned the right to speak here today.

1437
01:43:18.901 --> 01:43:20.068
Overruled.

1438
01:43:21.279 --> 01:43:22.904
Continue.

1439
01:43:25.658 --> 01:43:26.867
Go ahead, Dwayne.

1440
01:43:28.077 --> 01:43:30.328
I got a little girl.

1441
01:43:32.206 --> 01:43:34.875
Somebody rapes her, he's a dead dog.

1442
01:43:35.042 --> 01:43:37.252
I'll blow him away just like Carl Lee did.

1443
01:43:37.420 --> 01:43:38.628
Objection, Your Honor!

1444
01:43:38.796 --> 01:43:40.964
Do you think the jury
should convict Carl Lee?

1445
01:43:41.132 --> 01:43:43.425
Don't answer that question, deputy.

1446
01:43:43.593 --> 01:43:45.719
He's a hero. You turn him loose.

1447
01:43:45.887 --> 01:43:47.971
Jury will disregard.

1448
01:43:48.139 --> 01:43:49.389
Turn him loose!

1449
01:43:49.807 --> 01:43:52.058
Your Honor, you silence that witness!

1450
01:43:52.226 --> 01:43:54.227
Turn him loose!

1451
01:43:58.649 --> 01:43:59.774
No!

1452
01:44:01.652 --> 01:44:04.863
People say whatever the hell
they want in this courtroom!

1453
01:44:05.197 --> 01:44:06.740
Quiet!

1454
01:44:09.452 --> 01:44:11.828
Any more of that nonsense...

1455
01:44:11.996 --> 01:44:13.622
and you're all out of here.

1456
01:44:15.917 --> 01:44:18.752
Now, Mr. Buckley, you may begin.

1457
01:44:18.920 --> 01:44:20.962
Thank you, Your Honor.

1458
01:44:21.589 --> 01:44:26.217
Would you please state your name and
occupation for the members of the jury.

1459
01:44:26.385 --> 01:44:30.639
My name is Dr. Wilbert Rodeheaver,
chair of Psychiatry...

1460
01:44:30.806 --> 01:44:32.515
at Mississippi State University...

1461
01:44:32.683 --> 01:44:36.811
and clinical director of the Whitfield
Facility for the Criminally Insane.

1462
01:44:38.147 --> 01:44:41.066
Thank you, doctor.
Your credentials speak for themselves.

1463
01:44:41.233 --> 01:44:45.528
Now, doctor, can you please explain,
as you do so eloquently in your book...

1464
01:44:45.696 --> 01:44:47.864
the McNaughton Rule for the jury?

